==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: ka
<hw>ka</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Ancient Egyptian Religion)</fld> <def>A
spiritual aspect of the individual, living within the body during life,
and surviving the body after death. It was believed to be one of two
spirits inhabiting the body, the other being the <contr>ba</contr>,
which deserts teh body at death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kaaba</ent>⟦br⟧
